Britain's top female surfer has faced her biggest challenge yet after giving birth to a baby son two months early - just two days after a special photo-shoot to raise awareness of pre-natal health.

Pro surfer Hannah Harding 27, posed for a special set of pictures of her baby bump to raise awareness of the importance of keeping fit and exercising during pregnancy.

The pictures were designed to raise awareness of the issue, as part of Hannah's work for the charity Wave Project, which runs surf courses for socially isolated children.

